<TITLE> Massive hill slide in Teknaf kills 9 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Cox's Bazar, July 3 (bdnews24.com)  Nine people, including seven children of two families, died in a hill slide early Thursday, at Teknaf in Cox's Bazar, a police official said. Teknaf police chief Jasim Uddin told bdnews24.com the hill slide caused by torrential downpours hit a wide area, killing four members of one family at Dumparang in Teknaf sadar upazila and four members of another family at Fakiramura in Teknaf municipality around 3am. The ninth person was a guest staying with one of the families. The dead were identified as Khorsheda Begum (14), Morshed Alam (10), Nur Kalima (7) and Romeza Begum (2); Abu Tayob (36) and his three children Mofiz Alam (6), Rehena Akhter (10), Rashid Alam (4) and their guest Patan Ali. Upazila Nirbahi Officer Altaf Hossain Chowdhury visited the scenes of the disaster in the morning, Jasim said. Some 200 families dwell in the area hit by the massive slide, the police official said. They were asked to evacuate their homes, he added. bdnews24.
